The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Panel on fuel price reforms
                                                                                                               Panel on fuel price reforms
                            
	New Delhi, Sept. 3 (PTI): The government has formed a five-member committee, headed by Kirit S. Parikh, to suggest reforms in the pricing of auto and cooking fuels.        
	The expert group headed by Parikh will submit its recommendations in three months, petroleum secretary R.S. Pandey said.        
	Other members of the committee are Isher Judge Ahluwalia, chairperson of the Indian Council for Research on International Economic Relations, Suman K. Bery, director-general of the National Council of Applied Economic Research, and the secretaries of the finance and petroleum ministries.        
	This will be the third committee on fuel pricing. The recommendations of the previous committees  the C. Rangarajan committee and B.K. Chaturvedi committee  were not fully implemented.                                                                                                                                        
